      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(models): keep generated secret refs out of plaintext",
        "body": "Fixes #88562.\n\n## Summary\n\n- write generated env SecretRef-backed provider `apiKey` values as `secretref-env:<NAME>` markers instead of bare env-var names\n- teach generated model auth resolution to resolve those markers from the process environment\n- keep `openclaw security audit --deep` from treating generated env SecretRef markers as plaintext credentials\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Per-agent `models.json` generation could persist auth-profile env `keyRef` values as bare strings such as `TENSORIX_API_KEY`, which looked like plaintext to the deep security audit and produced false-positive `PLAINTEXT_FOUND` findings.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/andy/openclaw-88562`, branch `fix/models-json-secret-ref-88562`, commit `6954f219d5`.\n\nExact steps or command run after the patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/models-config.applies-config-env-vars.test.ts src/agents/models-config.providers.auth-aliases.test.ts src/agents/models-config.providers.auth-provenance.test.ts src/agents/models-config.providers.cloudflare-ai-gateway.test.ts src/agents/models-config.providers.normalize-keys.test.ts src/agents/models-config.providers.vercel-ai-gateway.test.ts src/agents/models-config.runtime-source-snapshot.test.ts src/agents/sessions/model-registry.test.ts src/secrets/audit.test.ts\ngit log --format='%h %an <%ae> %s' upstream/main..HEAD\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: The focused generator, model-registry, and audit tests passed, and the outgoing commit author was verified:\n\n```text\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  25 passed (25)\nTest Files  8 passed (8)\nTests  57 passed (57)\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 17.78s\n6954f219d5 Andy Ye <35905412+TurboTheTurtle@users.noreply.github.com> Fix models json secret ref api keys\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: A generated provider backed by an auth-profile env `keyRef` now gets `apiKey: \"secretref-env:TENSORIX_API_KEY\"`; `ModelRegistry` resolves that marker through `process.env.TENSORIX_API_KEY`, and the deep audit no longer reports `PLAINTEXT_FOUND` or unresolved SecretRef for that marker.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not run a live Tensorix provider request; runtime behavior is covered at the generated config and model registry credential-resolution boundary.\n",
        "branch": "fix/models-json-secret-ref-88562",
        "head_sha": "7215469a2fe52981a18ee35e6243c6f3875fe971",
